"4:35:13" : {s: 4, a: 35, w: 13, r: "رود", t: "يُرِيدَآ", l: "أَرَادَ", lc: 139, tl: "yurīdā", lb: "ইচ্ছা করা",e: "they both wish", b: "তারা চায়", i: "keduanya menghendaki", f: 1, rm: "to seek, ask a thing gently, search (for food), go to and fro in a pasture, go round about. iradatun - will, free will. mirwad - axle of a pully. rawada - to long after, desire, seduce, entice, seduce against the will (with an) as in 12:126. yuridu - he wishes, intends. It is used as an auxiliary verb as in 18:77. The word iradah is used for power and capacity with reference to subjugation as well as to option and choice. ruwaidan - for a little while, go gently (according to some grammarians the word is a diminutive form of which verbal noun is not in use, it is used as sing. plu. f. m.)."},
"4:35:14" : {s: 4, a: 35, w: 14, r: "صلح", t: "إِصْلَٰحًۭا", l: "إِصْلَٰح", lc: 7, tl: "iṣ'lāḥan", lb: "সংশোধন",e: "reconciliation", b: "আপোষ নিষ্পত্তি (করতে)", i: "perdamaian", f: 2, rm: "to be right/good/honest/upright/sound/righteous, suit, fit. aslaha - to set a thing aright, reform, do good. saalihaat - good works, fit and suiting deeds. aslaha (vb. 4) - to make whole sound, set things right, effect an agreement between, render fit. islaah - uprightness, reconciliation, amendment, reformation. muslihun - reformer, one who is upright, righteous, a person of integrity, peacemaker, suitable."},
"4:35:15" : {s: 4, a: 35, w: 15, r: "وفق", t: "يُوَفِّقِ", l: "يُوَفِّقِ", lc: 1, tl: "yuwaffiqi", lb: "",e: "will cause reconciliation", b: "(আল্লাহ) তৌফিক দিবেন", i: "akan memberi taufik", f: 1, rm: "to reconcile, to find suitable/fit/useful."},
"4:35:16" : {s: 4, a: 35, w: 16, r: "اله", t: "ٱللَّهُ", l: "ٱللَّه", lc: 2811, tl: "l-lahu", lb: "আল্লাহ",e: "Allah", b: "আল্লাহ", i: "Allah", f: 733, rm: "to serve, worship or adore; to protect, grant refuge, preserve save, rescue, liberate; object of worship ie God; (ا-ل-ل-ه) God, the one true God applied as a proper name denoting the true god, comprising all the excellent divine names; a unity comprising all the essences of existing things."},
