"4:35:20" : {s: 4, a: 35, w: 20, r: "كون", t: "كَانَ", l: "كَانَ", lc: 1358, tl: "kāna", lb: "হয়, হতো",e: "is", b: "আছে/হয়েছে/হয়", i: "adalah Dia", f: 323, rm: "To be, exist, happen, occur, take place, become, be such or so, originated."},
"4:35:21" : {s: 4, a: 35, w: 21, r: "علم", t: "عَلِيمًا", l: "عَلِيم", lc: 163, tl: "ʿalīman", lb: "পরম জ্ঞানী",e: "All-Knower", b: "মহাজ্ঞানী", i: "Maha mengetahui", f: 22, rm: "to mark/sign/distinguish, creations/beings, world, science/learning/knowledge/information, aware/know. By means of which one knows a thing, hence it signifies world or creation, because by it the Creator is known. alim (pl. ulama) - one who is learned/wise or knows."},
"4:35:22" : {s: 4, a: 35, w: 22, r: "خبر", t: "خَبِيرًۭا", l: "خَبِير", lc: 45, tl: "khabīran", lb: "সব জানেন",e: "All-Aware", b: "সর্ববিষয়ে জ্ঞাত", i: "Maha Mengerti", f: 12, rm: "To know/possess, have knowledge of a thing, to know a thing with respect to its internal or real state, informed/acquainted."},
