"4:36:17" : {s: 4, a: 36, w: 17, r: "جنب", t: "ٱلْجُنُبِ", l: "جُنُب", lc: 4, tl: "l-junubi", lb: "অপবিত্র, ভিনদেশী, বিদেশী, দূরবর্তী",e: "(who is) farther away", b: "দূর", i: "yang jauh", f: 1, rm: "To break or hit or hurt ones side, to lead one by his side, place or put a thing aside, to remove or send a thing far away or far off, estrange or alienate someone, descend and abode/settle as a stranger among people, to be remote/distant/far off/aloof from someone, shun or avoid someone, alienate or estrange oneself from someone, to be under the obligation of performing a total bath or ablution (by reason of sexual intercourse and semenal discharge), to be lateral or adjacent to someone or to a thing, walk by the side of another, to be gentle/compliant/easy to deal with, to be much of."},
"4:36:18" : {s: 4, a: 36, w: 18, r: "صحب", t: "وَٱلصَّاحِبِ", l: "صَاحِب", lc: 10, tl: "wal-ṣāḥibi", lb: "সাথী, সঙ্গী",e: "and the companion", b: "সঙ্গী-সাথী", i: "dan teman", f: 1, rm: "to company, associate, be the friend of or companion to. saahibun (pl. sahbuun and ashaabun) - companion, associate, possessor of any quality or thing, one in an intimate relation with anything, fellow and showing any type of connection or link, helper. saahibatun - spouse, consort, wife. saahaba - to bear company. ashaba (vb. 4) -to preserve, hinder, keep from, defend from. yushabuun - they will be accompanied."},
"4:36:19" : {s: 4, a: 36, w: 19, r: "جنب", t: "بِٱلْجَنۢبِ", l: "جَنب", lc: 8, tl: "bil-janbi", lb: "পার্শ্ব, প্রান্ত",e: "by your side", b: "নিকটবর্তী", i: "sejawat", f: 1, rm: "To break or hit or hurt ones side, to lead one by his side, place or put a thing aside, to remove or send a thing far away or far off, estrange or alienate someone, descend and abode/settle as a stranger among people, to be remote/distant/far off/aloof from someone, shun or avoid someone, alienate or estrange oneself from someone, to be under the obligation of performing a total bath or ablution (by reason of sexual intercourse and semenal discharge), to be lateral or adjacent to someone or to a thing, walk by the side of another, to be gentle/compliant/easy to deal with, to be much of."},
